						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in a field to the south of Mallēśvarasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>GAṆḌATRIṆĒTRA BAIDUṀBA VĪRAMAHĀRĀJU.</p>						

						<p>9th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated record can be assigned to the 9th century A.D., on the basis of palaeographical and internal evidences.</p>						

						<p>Refers to the death of <hi rend="italic">Pengāḷu</hi> Rāchamallunṟu, in a raid with a Bāṇa king <hi rend="italic">(Vāṇarāju)</hi> Raṇamorkka Siṅghaṁbu while the village Sadumbu was ruled by Lonkuḷāditya when Gaṇḍatrinētra B(V)aiduṁba Vīra mahārāju was ruling the country.</p>						

						</summary>
